<!--
  REVIEWED TRANSLATIONS — Step 6.M-A.3-R (2026-06-07)
  German (de) UI translations. Originally machine-drafted in Step
  6.M-A.3 (commit 26e8787) and then reviewed by native German
  speaker (Conrad).

  Key decisions made by Conrad:
   - Mood concept stays as "Stimmung".
   - "Achtsamkeit" used for mindfulness (German native term).
   - "Check-in" kept as English loanword for lightweight interactions;
     "Stimmungseintrag" or "Stimmungs-Check-in" used for clarity in
     some places.
   - "Einblicke" used for Insights (not "Erkenntnisse" / "Analyse").
   - "Elyria-Begleitung" (not "Elyria-Begleiter") — softer and less
     personified.
   - "Bewegung" (not "Sport") for the exercise trigger.
   - "du"-form throughout.
   - "Gut gemacht!" (not "Großartig gemacht!") for practice
     completion — natural and not exaggerated.

   - Emotions changed from nouns to ADJECTIVES in lowercase predicate
     form (grammatically correct in German, gender-neutral):
       traurig, ängstlich, wütend, müde, einsam, überfordert,
       ruhig, hoffnungsvoll, dankbar, stolz, friedlich, motiviert
     This differs from RU/UK/RO (which use nouns) but is natural for
     German chip-button UI per native speaker. Lowercase contrasts
     visually with other strings (which start with capital letters
     because they're nouns), but is grammatically required.

   - Space before ellipsis (e.g. "Startet …", "Elyria nimmt sich
     einen Moment …", "Elyria bereitet eine sanfte Reflexion vor …")
     is intentional German typography.

   - All 5 critical strings revised for naturalness:
     stronger and clearer disclaimer wording ("ersetzt keine" instead
     of "ist kein Ersatz für"), softer prompts with "Bitte" prefix
     where appropriate, "Hilfe" instead of "Begleitung" in the
     Companion safety disclaimer.

  No DRAFT markers remain. This file is release-ready for German.
-->
